    "While the authors concede that larger matrices often result in better likelihoods, they also note that it is common for this likelihood increase to plateau in practical scenarios.",
    "One can proceed to model selection regarding regression coefficients after determining dimension and structure.",
    "These coefficients align with the conventional system, allowing the use of AIC or BIC criteria for Comparison and selection among various proposed models.",
    "This study's approach focuses on achieving the fitting via log-likelihood.",
    "Additionally, the Bayesian optimization process, with its objective function defined as BIC = -2 × log-likelihood + num-params × np.log(n), where numparams = numclusters × (phases + 1) and n = length of data."
